Notable sites include: * '''Yoshitake Takagi Site''' ({{ill|Sawara-ku, Fukuoka|ja|早良区}}, Fukuoka): Found in Tomb 3 with two bronze swords, a bronze halberd, a bronze dagger-axe, and jade beads, resembling the {{ill|Imperial Regalia of Japan|ja|三種の神器|1=Imperial Regalia of Japan|lt=Three Sacred Treasures}}.<ref name="yayoinokaze"/> * '''Ōgōri Wakayama Site''' ({{ill|Ōgōri, Fukuoka|ja|小郡市}}, Nationally Designated Important Cultural Property)<ref name="ogori"/> * '''Uki Kumida Site''' ({{ill|Karatsu, Saga|ja|唐津市}}, Nationally Designated Important Cultural Property)<ref name="sadamori"/> * '''Masuda Site''' ({{ill|Saga City|ja|佐賀市}}, Prefectural Cultural Property)<ref name="saga"/> * '''Satodahara Site''' ({{ill|Hirado, Nagasaki|ja|平戸市}}, Prefectural Cultural Property)<ref name="hirado"/> * '''Kajikuri Beach Site''' ({{ill|Shimonoseki, Yamaguchi|ja|下関市}})<ref name="sadamori"/> * '''Nagura Site''' ({{ill|Gose, Nara|ja|御所市}}, Nationally Designated Important Cultural Property)<ref name="kobayashi"/> * '''Ōgōri Site''' ({{ill|Kashiwara, Osaka|ja|柏原市}}): Discovered during land development.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=Tachū Saimonkyō: A Mysterious Journey |url=http://www.city.kashiwara.osaka.jp/docs/2014082200249/?doc_id=1515|author=Kashiwara City Cultural Property Division |work=Kashiwara City |year= |accessdate=2022-09-11}}</ref>
=== Korea === Examples have been excavated from: * '''Bancheon-ri Site''' ({{ill|Pyongyang|ja|平壌}}, North Korea)<ref name="kobayashi"/> * '''Ipsil-ri Site''' ({{ill|Gyeongju, South Korea|ja|慶州市}}, South Korea)<ref name="kobayashi"/> == See Also == * {{ill|Yayoi period|ja|弥生時代}}
